essentialcraft.page.wind_0.txt=Magical wind. What is it? We all know it, we all had met it at some point in our lives, but what it actually is? Well, the answer is pretty simple!|The wind is somewhat of a living creature, that likes to observe people with unique fate!
essentialcraft.page.wind_1.txt=This effect you can get randomly just by doing random stuff in the world. It does nothing on it's own. It will only happen if you are bound to the wind!
essentialcraft.page.wind_2.txt=Wind mages can randomly spawn in your world.
essentialcraft.page.wind_3.txt=Wind mages occasionally drop these items. You can right-click them to release the trapped wind, and, therefore, increase your relations with it. Read the Enderstar section to learn how to bind yourself to the wind.
essentialcraft.page.wind_4.txt=Wind archmages rarely drop one of the armour pieces. Each piece of the armorset will increase the amount of wind relation points you gain from any source by 23%
essentialcraft.page.wind_5.txt=You can drink the Air Potion to increase the chance of random wind-related world events. The potions stack with themselves!
essentialcraft.page.drops_0.txt=You can use specific items on specific structures to harness the power of elements of nature into gems! Just create an appropriate structure and throw the required item in the middle. You can throw stacks, it does not matter. There is a 60% chance for elements to condense.
essentialcraft.page.drops_1.txt=To craft Fire Drops use Blaze powder.
essentialcraft.page.drops_2.txt=To craft Water Drops use Clay.
essentialcraft.page.drops_3.txt=To craft Earth Drops use Slime.
essentialcraft.page.drops_4.txt=To craft Air Drops use Gunpowder.
essentialcraft.page.drops_5.txt=You can craft elemental drops. They are used in lots of crafts. You can also craft different tools, but that will come later.
essentialcraft.page.miscCrafts_0.txt=All items and devices you want to craft are really complicated, and can't be crafted from simplest resources. This means, that you have to use some advanced items to make the devices. And here they are!
essentialcraft.page.mru_0.txt=Now we are getting close to the bases. What is MRU? Is this some kind of energy? In fact, here lies the answer to this question. It may be kinda complicated, so I warn you!
essentialcraft.page.mru_1.txt=First of all, as we all know everything consists of so called 'molecules'. And those molecules are created from bunch of even smaller particles - atoms. The atoms are not the smallest objects - they are made from some electrons, neutrons and protons.
essentialcraft.page.mru_2.txt=The atom represents a tiny solar system - it has a core, created from neutrons and protons, and electrons rotate around it in some form of layers. And this is not even it's 'final form'! It can be divided into even smaller objects, but we do not need to do so right now.
essentialcraft.page.mru_3.txt=Here is a hand-drawn imaginary model of an atom of a matter called 'Lithium'.
essentialcraft.page.mru_4.txt=The thing at the center represents the core, and the teal things are electrons. See anything unusual here? You should. There seems to be another particle, smaller than electrons, purplish color. What is it?
essentialcraft.page.mru_5.txt=And you have guessed correctly! Those particles are indeed MRU particles! MRU stands for Magical Radiation Unit. Let's try to get the meaning of those words. There is nothing to say about the fact, that it is a unit, but what about other words?
essentialcraft.page.mru_6.txt=Why is it Radiation? Because it behaves like γ particles! It radiates everything, sometimes doing bad things, but in general it does nothing for non-living stuff, and living creatures have a protection against it!
essentialcraft.page.mru_7.txt=Why is it magic then? Because it can, if it's central point of rotation changes transform one element into another! This particles seem to group with each other - at least, on the rotation speed and relative rotation point.
essentialcraft.page.mru_8.txt=This effect is called MRU Field. Basically, if there are come particles with odd rotation speed they can set the rotation speed of particles around them to their speed! This, as you can guess can lead to disasters!
essentialcraft.page.mru_9.txt=Thankfully, the MRU found in world is, pretty much, 100% balanced. It means, that it cannot harm anything, and will not change the matter around itself.
essentialcraft.page.mru_10.txt=As you can guess, the rotation speed is so called 'balance' of the MRU. If the particle rotates too slow or too fast it changes the central point of it's rotation, and can start harming everything around it.
essentialcraft.page.mru_11.txt=Sometimes, if too much unstable MRU leak into the world, the so called MRU Field becomes a little bit more global. They start creating so called 'MRUCU' - Magical Radiation Unit Concentration Unit. Lots of units there, huh?
essentialcraft.page.mru_12.txt=Here is a picture of a 100% balanced MRUCU. Yes, they exist too!
essentialcraft.page.mru_13.txt=Usually MRUCUs will get their balance shifted to one or other side. There is another problem - you simply cannot SEE the MRUCUs! There are items, that allow you to see them, but you can't make them now. 
essentialcraft.page.mru_14.txt=However, you can HEAR MRUCUs! They make a little noise, that you can hear, if you listen carefully. If MRUCU is pretty big it will start corrupting the world around itself.|It is also known, that standing near MRUCUs without any protection may lead to some nasty effects...
essentialcraft.page.mru_15.txt=You can simply break those corruption blocks, just do not stand in them for too long! You can also MOVE MRUCUs using MRUCU Moving Wands. They break after some time too. To pull MRUCUs hold rightclick, and to push them also hold SHIFT.
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_0.txt=Every living thing has 'MRU Matrix'. This matrix cannot be seen or otherwise known of, and it serves as a protection from various MRU effects. However, there is a way to see the numeric representation of your matrix - the Soul Stone!
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_1.txt=To make a Soul Stone throw some emeralds on an emerald block surrounded by soul sand.
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_2.txt=To make the soul stone read information bound it to yourself by right-clicking.
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_3.txt=Now, the lines represent your matrix. The second line represents the amount of MRU stored in your matrix. The last line represents the balance of your matrix, and the first one represents the player the stone is bound to. You will need this stone later on, so keep it!
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_4.txt=You can increase the amount of MRU in your matrix by killing living creatures. Every time a creature dies you get a chance to absorb some of it's matrix energy. The more max health the mob had, the more MRU you will get as a result.
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_5.txt=It is worth mentioning, that if you die you lose ALL MRU energy in your matrix, and have to start all over again. On the other hand, if a player kills another player ALL MRU energy from the victim will go to the killer.
essentialcraft.page.soulStone_6.txt=If you have Blood Magic installed, you can imbue the Soul Stone with blood using altar(tier 1 is enough), and the result will be the same soul stone, that is able to tell your Life Network!
essentialcraft.page.book_0.txt=Welcome to EssentialCraft, and to the amazing and long-waited Book Of Knowledge! Here I will tell you almost all you need to know to play with EssentialCraft!
essentialcraft.page.book_1.txt=And the most important thing is of course the book! 
essentialcraft.page.book_2.txt=The book is pretty easy to navigate. It is divided by categories. The book itself has a tier based system, so you will need to update it using specific crafts and rituals. Every new tier unlocks you a new category.
essentialcraft.page.book_3.txt=Every category has a name and a short description. Basically, if you need to lookup something basic, that you can get without playing with EssentialCraft - look in the Basic section. If you need to look up a machine - Magical Engineering is there!
essentialcraft.page.book_4.txt=Each category contains some 'discoveries' - sections of specific information. They also have both the name and a short description. If you mouse over any category, you can see, how many discoveries are in there.
essentialcraft.page.book_5.txt=Every discovery contains a certain amount of pages with different information on them. It can be straight up plain text, as here. It can be a crafting recipe of any kind, including structures! It can also be an image, or just a set of items.
essentialcraft.page.book_6.txt=Items on pages can sometimes be left-clicked, if there is a recipe for such item. However, if you can not craft the item, but the displayed item has a Goto in it's description it will most likely browse you to the page, where that item is displayed.
essentialcraft.page.book_7.txt=If you want to go back (for example you've read enough of this and want to lookup some information about MRU) there is an orange pointer in the top right corner of the book. The book is also fully controllable by the keyboard - try it out by pressing your arrow keys, backspace and things like ctrl. You can even input the number of the discovery/category to go to with your number keys and press enter!
essentialcraft.page.book_8.txt=You can close the book any time you want, do something, and when you open it it will stay at the same page you were on. Unless you close your game.
essentialcraft.page.book_9.txt=When browsing a recipe you may want to lookup a recipe for an item, that is used in the craft you are interested in. If that item has a recipe, you can left-click it, and you will be shown the exact recipe you are looking for.
essentialcraft.page.book_10.txt=If you want to go back to the first thing you want to craft (the page you've left by left-clicking) you can right-click the screen in any place to go back. The way you go through the book is stored infinitely.
essentialcraft.page.book_11.txt=On the title page there is a line, that says Edition. The numbers below are your version of EssentialCraft.
essentialcraft.page.book_12.txt=If you want to lookup a quick recipe/information about a block in the world just point at the block and press R on your keyboard.
essentialcraft.page.book_13.txt=The same rule applies to items - if an item lays on the ground you can look it up using the book.
essentialcraft.page.book_14.txt=You can lookup recipes/info about blocks and items even if you do not have the required tier of a book.
essentialcraft.page.book_15.txt=This is how you upgrade your book to tier 2. Thanks and have fun!
essentialcraft.page.decorations_0.txt=You can create lots of decorative blocks using the Magical Chisel! There are some variations, and you can create your own, using the config file! It is also possible to use those blocks in the corresponding structures, just like before chiseling.
essentialcraft.page.overworld_0.txt=The world has changed - it is not the same as it used to be. You can find some structures, that appear to be a part of some other MRU scientists from the past... Seems like deep, deep past, a very long time ago. They usually have a MRUCU in their center. They may also have some chests with fancy loot in them!
essentialcraft.page.overworld_1.txt=In different chests around your world you may find some interesting items - rings, amulets and belts. They can't be replicated - the technology seems lost, but you can use what is left. They all have a description, that tells you exactly what they do.
 
