essentialcraft.page.radiation_0.txt=Not looking so hot, eh? It was all a lie, after all. The "world of great opportunities", the "place of technology and magic mixed, combined and fully functional", the "land of dreams"... Is a NUCLEAR DESERT. What happened? Who knows, but this place is, for sure, a dangerous one!
essentialcraft.page.radiation_1.txt=Scorching sun, empty destroyed cities and underground catacombs - this place is a terrible one. The air itself is poisoned, and if you breath it for too long - you will die. 
essentialcraft.page.radiation_2.txt=Different areas seem more poisoned, than the others, sometimes you can find an area to rest, with it's air almost clear. And some areas make your lungs set on fire from a single breath of air.
essentialcraft.page.radiation_3.txt=There is no cure for radiation, and no way of removing it. If you got affected by it - time is your only panacea. No magical "milk drinking", no "amulets".
essentialcraft.page.radiation_4.txt=However, some special constructed armor may help you with fighting that radiation. For example, the Magical Hazmat Suit one. Just be sure to wear a full set - otherwise it is as useless as an Iron armor in this world.
essentialcraft.page.radiation_5.txt=Sometimes the loot in this world contains some baubles - the seem to help with fighting radiation too!
essentialcraft.page.radiation_6.txt=This world is a dreadful place - sometimes those "events" occurs. Like, it is suddenly so dark, that you can barely see your hand! Or the opposite - it is so bright, that everything, including air is burning! And sometimes the poisonous gas comes from the cracks in the ground...
essentialcraft.page.radiation_7.txt=Overall - this place is really dangerous, yet it may yield lots of interesting loot!
essentialcraft.page.loot_0.txt=The Hoanna contains remains of past civilizations - they left some loot! Rarely, in towns or underground you can find chests with different items in them!
essentialcraft.page.voidStone_0.txt=Different materials you've found in Hoanna allow to create much more advanced blocks, which can almost fully negate MRU flowing through them. You sure can use them for some things!
essentialcraft.page.voidArmor_0.txt=This set of armor proves to be the best in the game. It makes you almost immune to radiation and MRU effects, it increases your max health by 20, it gives you various buffs, it is nearly unbreakable, better than diamond and has the best enchantability!
essentialcraft.page.magicalTeleporter_0.txt=This structure is able to teleport the player ANY DISTANCE !INCLUDING! different DIMENSIONS! Just place this structure anywhere, use the bound gem to set a location to teleport to, supply this device with MRU and place the bound gem in the second slot. Now step in the middle, and see, what happens!
essentialcraft.page.magicalTeleporter_2.txt=Row 0. A 5x5 layer of Void Stone with a teleporter in the middle
essentialcraft.page.magicalTeleporter_3.txt=Row 1. Row 1 means that it is higher than row 0 by 1 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.magicalTeleporter_4.txt=Row 2. Row 2 means that it is higher than row 0 by 2 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.magicalFurnace_0.txt=This structure is able to smelt items thrown on top of it just like the regular furnace would. But it takes around 0.8 second to smelt an item, has a 30% chance of doubling the outcome and produces Magical Slags.
essentialcraft.page.magicalFurnace_2.txt=Row 0. A 5x5 layer of Void Stone.
essentialcraft.page.magicalFurnace_3.txt=Row 1. Row 1 means that it is higher than row 0 by 1 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.magicalFurnace_4.txt=Row 2. Row 2 means that it is higher than row 0 by 2 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.emberForge_0.txt=This structure allows the production of so called "Elemental Swords". Basically, throw some Elemental Foci at the Magic Plating Blocks, and then throw some Embers you found in the dungeons on the Pale Plating blocks, wait for it to be night time... and wait a little bit.
essentialcraft.page.emberForge_2.txt=Row 0. A 5x5 layer of Void Stone.
essentialcraft.page.emberForge_3.txt=Row 1. Row 1 means that it is higher than row 0 by 1 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.emberForge_4.txt=Row 2. Row 2 means that it is higher than row 0 by 2 on Y axis.
essentialcraft.page.mim_0.txt=You can create a system, that will allow you to manage the inventories all among your base. This system consists of some devices, each serves it's functionalities.
essentialcraft.page.mim_2.txt=Filter. This filter can be opened by right-clicking it in your hand. In the GUI you have 9 slots. In each you can put any item, and it will be filtered by other devices in the system. Putting a filter in a filter will allow you to specify more items.
essentialcraft.page.mim_4.txt=Advanced Filter. This filter functions the same way as the previous one does, except, that you can specify, if you want to ignore Metadata, NBTData, or you can check items by Ore Dictionary, and not their IDs.
essentialcraft.page.mim_7.txt=Ejection Nodes - you can use this to eject items out of inventories. If you use the basic one you need to attach this to the side you want to extract the items from. Putting a filter in the top slot will make the ejector to eject only items, which are stated in the filter.
essentialcraft.page.mim_8.txt=Advanced Ejection Node allows you to specify the slot to pull items from. The side you are attaching this device to does not matter. It is also possible to eject items from slots, from which items can't normally be ejected.
essentialcraft.page.mim_11.txt=Injection Nodes - work the same way as the ejection ones, but they Insert items into slots, instead of ejecting them.
essentialcraft.page.mim_13.txt=The manager itself is a core of the system. You need to supply it with MRU, and then, you need to link every device in your systems(nodes) with bound gems. After that put your bound gems in this device in the order, you want them to be accessed.
essentialcraft.page.o8elisk_0.txt=This device forces monsters to spawn near8y. It will spawn 8iome-specific monsters too! If you place a spawner in it's 8ottom slot, it will instead function just like that spawner! It does not requires players to 8e near8y to function, which is gr8 for your spawning systems! 
essentialcraft.page.ultraHeat_0.txt=This is a straight upgrade over the Heat Generator. It functions just the same way, except for the fact, that it requires time to heat up, and the more it is heated up, the more MRU it produces. There is no heat limit too! The more it's heated, the less fuel it will consume.
essentialcraft.page.ultraFlower_0.txt=This is a straight upgrade over the Natural Furnace. This device functions the same way as the regular Natural Furnace does, except for the fact, that it creates much more MRU, does not burn saplings, but burns leaves and logs, and automatically replants all the saplings dropped by burned leaves!
 
 
